        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>16 Little Britain (City)</placeName>
                    <date>March 10/76</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I enclose cheque on Union Bank for <hi rend="underline">£35.13.8</hi> in payment of above a/c which please acknowledge &amp; oblige<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>Yours Respectfully | Charles Layton | Agent D. Appleton &amp; Co <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/></p>
<p rend="left">Charles Darwin Esq <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/></p>
<p><hi rend="underline">The Stereo Plates N.E Variation of Plants &amp; Animals</hi> have been sent to New York, <hi rend="doubleUnderline">since</hi> Feby 18 <hi rend="underline">date of letter opposite—</hi><ref target="#foot.f2"/></p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The payment was for the royalties for the US editions of CD’s works; see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-10401.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from D. Appleton &amp; Co., 18 February 1876</ref>. CD recorded the receipt of £35 13<hi rend="italic">s.</hi> 8<hi rend="italic">d.</hi> in his Account books–banking account (Down House MS) on 11 March 1876.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">The letter was written on the verso of the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-10401.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from D. Appleton &amp; Co., 18 February 1876</ref>. Layton refers to the stereotype plates for the second (new) edition of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_7951.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Variation</hi></ref>.</note>
        </div>        
            
